cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Baton — a local coordination hub for multiple AI coding agents"
message: "If you use Baton in your research or work, please cite it using this metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Shetty
    given-names: Rakshan
repository-code: "https://github.com/Rakshan001/Baton-Multi-Agent-"
url: "https://baton-landing.vercel.app"
abstract: >-
  Baton is a local coordination hub and knowledge base for running multiple AI
  coding agents on one repository. It provides isolated git worktrees, a
  realtime dashboard over Server-Sent Events, edit-signal coordination, a
  queryable code knowledge graph, shared evidence-anchored memory, installable
  skills, and one-file session handoff between agents.
keywords:
  - ai-agents
  - coding-agents
  - developer-tools
  - git-worktrees
  - knowledge-graph
  - agent-handoff
  - llm
  - cli
